AGI -&nbsp;A UN investigation concluded that Israel performed "genocide" acts in Gaza through "systemic" attacks on reproductive health. The United Nations Commission of Inquiry stated that Israel "intentionally attacked and destroyed" the main fertility center of the Palestinian territory and simultaneously imposed a siege and blocked aid, including drugs to ensure pregnancy, parts and safe neonatal care. "Israel categorically rejects unfounded accusations," said his mission in Geneva in a statement.
&nbsp;
The committee found that the Israeli authorities "destroyed in part the reproductive capacity of the Palestinians in Gaza as a group through the systematic destruction of sexual and reproductive health care," the UN said that this was equivalent to "two categories of genocide." &nbsp;
<h2>Netanyahu, false and absurd accusations UN of genocidal acts
False and absurd statements are the UN charges that Israel has made "genocides" in Gaza through "systemic" attacks on reproductive health. Israeli prime minister Benjamin Netanyahu said so.
&nbsp;
"The anti-Israeli circle known as the UN Human Rights Council once again chose to attack the State of Israel with false accusations, including absurd statements on the destruction of sexual and reproductive health structures in Gaza," reads in a note widespread by Netanyahu's office.
&nbsp;
The Israeli prime minister called the Council "an anti-Semitic organ, rotten, supporter of terrorists and irrelevant". "Instead of focusing on the crimes of war and against humanity committed by the Hamas terrorist organization in the worst massacre committed against the Jewish people by the Holocaust, the UN is once again choosing to attack Israel with false accusations, including unfounded accusations of sexual violence," adds the Israeli prime minister.
&nbsp;
Tel Aviv's Foreign Ministry, in a message about X, spoke instead of "one of the worst cases of blood slander the world has ever seen, and has seen so many." With the term "blood slander", whose meaning was later extended in contemporary times, we refer to the accusations made in recent centuries to Jews to use blood of Christian victims, often children, for their religious rituals. The UN report, according to the ministry, "promotes victims of crimes committed against them. Hamas is the organization that has committed horrible sexual crimes against the Israelis. It is really a disgusting document that only an anti-Semitic organization like the UN could produce." &nbsp;
<h2>Hamas, UN report demonstrates genocide Israel
Hamas spokesman, Hazem Qassem, said that the report of the UN Committee of Inquiry shows that Israel committed a "genocide" in the Palestinian territory after the October 7 attack. Qassem stressed that "the report on acts of genocide against the Palestinian people confirms what happened in the field: genocide and violation of all humanitarian and legal principles."

